"Servicing stack updates must **ship separately** from the cumulative updates because they modify the component that installs Windows updates. The servicing stack is **released separately** because the servicing stack itself requires an update."

Is this still true?

Deploy Windows SSUs and LCUs **together** with one cumulative update

https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/windows-it-pro-blog/deploy-windows-ssus-and-lcus-together-with-one-cumulative-update/ba-p/1967887


